>
> He stares at Magmatron with a thunderous roar in his voice.

<NEW>

"He is quite loud isn't he." SABERBACK said as he winced from the
thunderous volume in TUSCON's voice.

"He has always been a loud mouth! I remember him from my days on
Cybertron." DARK RODIMUS said as he pointed at TUSCON, his optics
blazing in response to the roar. "This new form has just made it more
obvious!"

HARDHEAD and HYDRA were about to hit TUSCON with the butt of their
weapons when MAGMATRON held up his hand. "No, do not harm him." He
said, his voice full of amusement, he did not seem to be as much
affected by the volume as SABERBACK or DARK RODIMUS.  "At least not
yet."

HARDHEAD and HYDRAS both nodded as they lowered their weapons and
GUILEDART resumed his standing posture.

"What shall we do with him my lord?" GUILEDART said, looking up at the
much taller MAGMATRON.

Smiling MAGMATRON folded his arms over his chest. "tell me my dark
knight, will he do well in the games?" He glanced at DARK RODIMUS

DARK RODIMUS looked at TUSCON speculatively, much like one might
examine a horse or a dog before a purchase. "Perhaps. He has always
been a maverick. Maybe it will be put to better use there."

"Good. have him taken to the pens and made ready." MAGMATRON said as
he looked back at GUILEDART.

MAGMATRON glanced over at SABERBACK as he detected a slight frown.
"Don't worry, you will be able to have your fun with him."

MAGMATRON turned to address TUSCON, "Oh and yes, all of you start out
this way. Full of themselves." He smiled, "I love to see it. It means
you will be around for a while."

(TAG)

Preston
